### Restaurant Reservation API — manual test flow
### Use with the VS Code "REST Client" extension (humao.rest-client).
### Click "Send Request" above each block, top to bottom.
### Tokens are captured automatically into variables between requests.

@baseUrl = http://localhost:5000

### 0. Health check
GET {{baseUrl}}/health

### 1a. Register a customer  -> 201
# @name registerCustomer
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Alice Customer",
  "email": "alice@example.com",
  "password": "secret123"
}

### 1b. Log in as the customer -> 200, capture token
# @name loginCustomer
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "alice@example.com",
  "password": "secret123"
}

###
@customerToken = {{loginCustomer.response.body.token}}

### (helper) See which tables exist / are available for the slot -> 200
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/tables/available?date=2026-12-31&timeSlot=19:00&guests=2
Authorization: Bearer {{customerToken}}

### 2. Create a reservation (table 3 = capacity 4) -> 201
# @name createReservation
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/reservations
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{customerToken}}

{
  "table": "PASTE_TABLE_3_ID_HERE",
  "date": "2026-12-31",
  "timeSlot": "19:00",
  "guests": 2
}

### 3. Double-book SAME table/date/slot -> 409 conflict
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/reservations
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{customerToken}}

{
  "table": "PASTE_TABLE_3_ID_HERE",
  "date": "2026-12-31",
  "timeSlot": "19:00",
  "guests": 2
}

### 4. Guests > table capacity (table 3 holds 4, ask for 10) -> 400
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/reservations
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{customerToken}}

{
  "table": "PASTE_TABLE_3_ID_HERE",
  "date": "2026-12-31",
  "timeSlot": "20:00",
  "guests": 10
}

### 5. Past date -> 400
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/reservations
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{customerToken}}

{
  "table": "PASTE_TABLE_3_ID_HERE",
  "date": "2020-01-01",
  "timeSlot": "19:00",
  "guests": 2
}

### 6a. Log in as admin -> 200, capture token
# @name loginAdmin
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "admin@example.com",
  "password": "admin1234"
}

###
@adminToken = {{loginAdmin.response.body.token}}

### 6b. Admin GET all reservations -> 200
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/reservations
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

### 6c. Admin GET all reservations filtered by date -> 200
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/reservations?date=2026-12-31
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

### 7. Customer hits an admin-only route -> 403 forbidden
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/reservations
Authorization: Bearer {{customerToken}}
